ngland, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"nl":{"Abt 1109–":"circa 1109–Overleden","1109–Male":"1109–Overleden","1112–Female":"1112–Overleden","1135–1197":"1135–1197","–1180":"–1180","1087–1125":"1087–1125","1089–Female":"1089–Overleden","1125":"1125","before 1135":"vóór 1135","1135":"1135","1112":"1112","1089":"1089","1087":"1087","1197":"1197","before 1109":"vóór 1109","Abt 1109":"circa 1109","1109":"1109","1180":"1180","Bourton, Oxfordshire, England":"Bourton, Oxfordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Tetsworth, Oxfordshire, England":"Tetsworth, Oxfordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England":"England"},"en":{"Abt 1109–":"about 1109–Deceased","1109–Male":"1109–Deceased","1112–Female":"1112–Deceased","1135–1197":"1135–1197","–1180":"–1180","1087–1125":"1087–1125","1089–Female":"1089–Deceased","1125":"1125","before 1135":"before 1135","1135":"1135","1112":"1112","1089":"1089","1087":"1087","1197":"1197","before 1109":"before 1109","Abt 1109":"about 1109","1109":"1109","1180":"1180","Bourton, Oxfordshire, England":"Bourton, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom","Tetsworth, Oxfordshire, England":"Tetsworth, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"d'Anvers","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Fitzroy.","English (Leicestershire): of Norman origin, a habitational name with fused preposition <i>d(e)</i> for someone from <i>Anvers</i>, the French name of the port of Antwerp in what is now Belgium."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert d'Anvers I was born about 1109, in Bourton, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Geoffrey d'Anvers, was 24 and his mother, Mrs Geoffrey Danvers, was 22. He married Mrs Robert d'Anvers before 1135, in England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons."},"et":{"Abt 1109–":"umbes 1109–Surnud","1109–Male":"1109–Surnud","1112–Female":"1112–Surnud","1135–1197":"1135–1197","–1180":"–1180","1087–1125":"1087–1125","1089–Female":"1089–Surnud","1125":"1125","before 1135":"enne 1135","1135":"1135","1112":"1112","1089":"1089","1087":"1087","1197":"1197","before 1109":"enne 1109","Abt 1109":"umbes 1109","1109":"1109","1180":"1180","Bourton, Oxfordshire, England":"Bourton, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Tetsworth, Oxfordshire, England":"Tetsworth, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"fi":{"Abt 1109–":"noin 1109–Kuollut","1109–Male":"1109–Kuollut","1112–Female":"1112–Kuollut","1135–1197":"1135–1197","–1180":"–1180","1087–1125":"1087–1125","1089–Female":"1089–Kuollut","1125":"1125","before 1135":"ennen vuotta 1135","1135":"1135","1112":"1112","1089":"1089","1087":"1087","1197":"1197","before 1109":"ennen vuotta 1109","Abt 1109":"noin 1109","1109":"1109","1180":"1180","Bourton, Oxfordshire, England":"Bourton, Oxfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Tetsworth, Oxfordshire, England":"Tetsworth, Oxfordshire, Englan